d to its alternatives, as well as to the early elaboration of the machine that would become the ultimate guarantor of modern dance’s de-mechanization, the motion picture camera.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Dance / Modern.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361904340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503619043423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503619043/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles